{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   Adaptation User Message Template
   Variables: channel, channel_constraints (json), audience, audience_tone,
              rules_text, content
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
Adapt the following source content for the specified channel and audience.

TARGET CHANNEL: {{ channel }}
CHANNEL CONSTRAINTS: {{ channel_constraints }}

TARGET AUDIENCE: {{ audience }}
AUDIENCE TONE GUIDANCE: {{ audience_tone }}

BRAND RULES TO RESPECT:
{{ rules_text }}

SOURCE CONTENT:
{{ content }}

Return a JSON object with:
- "adapted_content": the fully adapted content string (plain text, use line breaks for paragraphs)
- "word_count": integer word count of the adapted content
- "change_log": array of change objects, each with:
  - "original_text": text from the source that was changed
  - "changed_text": what it was changed to
  - "change_type": one of "terminology", "tone", "structure", "cta", "claim", "formatting"
  - "rule_reference": the rule_id or section that drove this change
  - "rationale": brief explanation of why

Include EVERY meaningful change in the change_log. Do not omit changes.
The adapted content MUST be within the word count limit.
Use ONLY approved CTA phrasing for this channel. If no CTA is allowed, omit any CTA.
